<subSubSection id="62DB80FBFF84FFB3FF70B84EFEC2FB74" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2A7ED370FF84FFB3FF70B84EFEC2FB74" blockId="2.[151,760,1075,1418]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
<emphasis id="18B50F62FF84FFB3FF70B84EFE9BFBD4" bold="true" box="[151,268,1075,1098]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus can be recognized by a combination of the following characteristics of the worker caste: i) prominent costate sculpture on most of body surface, ii) large eyes, iii) exposed antennal sockets, iv) two spurs on mid and hind tibiae, and v) pretarsal claws with a tooth (
<bibRefCitation id="4E50AE81FF84FFB3FF78B8AEFEDDFB74" author="BOROWIEC M. L." box="[159,330,1235,1258]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" pagination="1 - 280" part="608" refId="ref9376" refString="BOROWIEC M. L. 2016: Generic revision of the ant subfamily Dorylinae (Hymenoptera, Formicidae). ZooKeys 608: 1 - 280." title="Generic revision of the ant subfamily Dorylinae (Hymenoptera, Formicidae)" type="journal article" year="2016">BOROWIEC 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="62DB80FBFF84FFB3FF70B88EFD6FFA14" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2A7ED370FF84FFB3FF70B88EFD6FFA14" blockId="2.[151,760,1075,1418]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
<emphasis id="18B50F62FF84FFB3FF70B88EFD6FFA94" bold="true" box="[151,760,1266,1290]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Key to 
<taxonomicName id="EDC1A8F3FF84FFB3FF0DB88FFE56FA94" box="[234,449,1266,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Chrysapace" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="18B50F62FF84FFB3FF0DB88FFEFCFA94" bold="true" box="[234,363,1266,1290]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">Chrysapace</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
based onthe worker caste.
</emphasis>
The key to valid species is provided below. Known distribution is shown in the parentheses after species name. Our knowledge on 
<taxonomicName id="EDC1A8F3FF84FFB3FEC8B92EFE24FAF4" authorityName="Crawley" authorityYear="1924" box="[303,435,1362,1386]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Chrysapace" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacobsoni">
<emphasis id="18B50F62FF84FFB3FEC8B92EFE24FAF4" box="[303,435,1362,1386]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">C. jacobsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on its original description (
<bibRefCitation id="4E50AE81FF84FFB3FF2AB90EFEFDFA14" author="CRAWLEY W. C." box="[205,362,1395,1418]" firstAuthor="CRAWLEY" journalOrPublisher="Annals and Magazine of Natural History" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" pagination="380 - 409" part="13" refId="ref9568" refString="CRAWLEY W. C. 1924: Ants from Sumatra, with biological notes by Edward Jacobson. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 9 13: 380 - 409" title="Ants from Sumatra, with biological notes by Edward Jacobson" type="journal article" year="1924">CRAWLEY 1924</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="4E50AE81FF84FFB3FE9DB90EFDBFFA14" author="WHEELER W. M." box="[378,552,1395,1418]" firstAuthor="WHEELER" journalOrPublisher="Psyche (Cambridge)" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" pagination="224 - 225" part="31" refId="ref9995" refString="WHEELER W. M. 1924: On the ant-genus Chrysapace Crawley. Psyche (Cambridge) 31: 224 - 225." title="On the ant-genus Chrysapace Crawley" type="journal article" year="1924">WHEELER (1924)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="4E50AE81FF84FFB3FDBBB90EFD63FA14" author="BROWN W. L. Jr." box="[604,756,1395,1418]" firstAuthor="BROWN" journalOrPublisher="Search Agriculture (Ithaca, New York)" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" pagination="1 - 115" part="5" refId="ref9471" refString="BROWN W. L. Jr. 1975: Contributions toward a reclassification of the Formicidae. V. Ponerinae, tribes Platythyreini, Cerapachyini, Cylindromyrmecini, Acanthostichini, andAenictogitini. Search Agriculture (Ithaca, New York) 5 (1): 1 - 115." title="Contributions toward a reclassification of the Formicidae. V. Ponerinae, tribes Platythyreini, Cerapachyini, Cylindromyrmecini, Acanthostichini, andAenictogitini" type="journal article" year="1975">BROWN (1975)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
